							</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<!-- What This Blog Is Section -->
				<div class="mb-16">
					<h2 class="text-4xl font-semibold mb-12 victoria-font"
						style="font-family: 'Victoria', 'Times New Roman', serif; color: #2F4858;">
						What This Blog Is
					</h2>
					
					<div class="space-y-6">
						<p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
							The Money-Printing Press is my attempt at preserving ideas that feel worth preserving while challenging the ones that don't.
						</p>
						<p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
							Some posts will read like personal essays. Others will be sharper, shorter reflections. You'll find thoughts on history, money, behavior, books, travel, culture, and more â€” all filtered through the lens of someone trying to build a good life with his eyes wide open.
						</p>
						<p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
							There's no publishing schedule or promise of perfection. But there is effort. Every post here has been written with care and a sense of duty â€” to clarity, to honesty, and to the idea that better thinking leads to better living.
						</p>
						<p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
							This is a quiet corner on the internet. No fluff, no ragebait, no click-churn. Just thought, in print.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<!-- Follow on Socials Section -->
				<div class="p-12 rounded-2xl" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #9e383d, #7f1d1d);">
					<h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-white mb-6 victoria-font">
						Follow on Socials!
					</h2>
					<p class="text-gray-200 mb-8 max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
						Stay connected and get the latest insights on wealth through the ages. 
